sentences: Mabel Alabama-Pearl McVey (born 20 February 1996) is a British-Swedish singer and songwriter.
In 2017, she had her breakthrough with "Finders Keepers", peaking at number eight on the UK Singles Chart.
Her debut studio album, High Expectations (2019), entered the UK Albums Chart at number three and was certified platinum.
Mabel won the Brit Award for British Female Solo Artist in 2020.
Mabel Alabama-Pearl McVey was born on 19 February 1996 in Alhaurín el Grande, Málaga, Spain.
The family lived in Alhaurín el Grande for two years prior to Mabel's birth before relocating back to Notting Hill, West London, England, when she was age two.
The following year, she learned piano and wrote her first song.
